  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      High sodium intake causes hypertension. Various efforts for reducing salt consumption are
      proceeding all over the world. Solar salt contains reduced sodium and abundant mineral, such
      as calcium, potassium, and magnesium, comparing to ordinary salt. Use of solar salt, instead
      of ordinary salt, may have beneficial effects to blood pressure.

      The investigators are going to conduct a preliminary study that can support antihypertensive
      effect of solar salt intake.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
